The cleanest bash way I found is

    public_libraries_path="${ANDROID_PRODUCT_OUT}/.../public.libraries.txt"
    make_command+=" ${public_libraries_path#$(readlink -f $PWD/)}"                

but it is not very portable because of `readlink` having a different behaviour on BSD and OSX.

